00:20:13.670 --> 00:20:14.970
&gt;&gt; Bill Roorbach: Sound good to me.

00:20:14.970 --> 00:20:16.270
&gt;&gt; Brad Watson: Okay.

00:20:16.270 --> 00:20:17.570
[ Laughter ]

00:20:17.570 --> 00:20:18.870
&gt;&gt; Bill Roorbach: I'd
love to hear you read.

00:20:18.870 --> 00:20:23.510
&gt;&gt; Brad Watson: I don't
want to take too much time.

00:20:23.510 --> 00:20:24.810
Okay. This is -- all right.

00:20:24.810 --> 00:20:28.160
So I had to imagine how my
great aunt might have gone

00:20:28.160 --> 00:20:29.520
to these dances.

00:20:29.520 --> 00:20:36.000
And I thought, "Well, how did
she go without having an accident

00:20:36.000 --> 00:20:37.700
as she calls it in the book?"

00:20:37.700 --> 00:20:40.740
And so I just thought, I
said, "Well, what would I do?"

00:20:40.740 --> 00:20:49.510
And this is about that,
her first dance.

00:20:51.160 --> 00:20:55.850
For an entire two days before the
evening of the dance, she fasted.

00:20:55.850 --> 00:20:59.100
First thing on the first morning
she dosed herself with castor oil,

00:20:59.100 --> 00:21:02.750 position:56%
followed by a little buttermilk just
to have something on her stomach

00:21:02.750 --> 00:21:06.000
and stayed in the privy until
she felt herself emptied out.

00:21:06.000 --> 00:21:09.330
She spent the next entire day
beneath the tree in the middle

00:21:09.330 --> 00:21:12.910
of the pecan grove or beside the
fishing pond or lying in the middle

00:21:12.910 --> 00:21:15.290
of her favorite little
clearing in the woods.

00:21:15.290 --> 00:21:17.500
She would take along a
piece of bread, maybe bacon

00:21:17.500 --> 00:21:21.650
but scatter the bread for the
birds, toss the bacon to the fish,

00:21:21.650 --> 00:21:28.260 position:56%
not thinking -- just being or simply
being Jane as when she was younger.

00:21:28.260 --> 00:21:29.930
On the first day she
would allow herself

00:21:29.930 --> 00:21:32.370
to sip a little water
from time to time.

00:21:32.370 --> 00:21:35.640
At some point in the second
day there would be an almost

00:21:35.640 --> 00:21:39.060
hallucinatory clarity in her
vision, in the presence of things

00:21:39.060 --> 00:21:44.120
around her, in the sounds of birds
and farm work and dogs barking,

00:21:44.120 --> 00:21:47.340
sounds of livestock
and people talking.

00:21:47.340 --> 00:21:50.950
Even the breezes gently rustling
leaves in the trees made a sound

00:21:50.950 --> 00:21:53.810
that seemed to fill her
mind in an intoxicating way,

00:21:53.810 --> 00:21:57.330
as if the very tips of the leaves
were tickling her awareness.

00:21:57.330 --> 00:22:01.400
The temptation of the senses that
she allowed to wash through her,

00:22:01.400 --> 00:22:04.500 position:56%
to flush her with calm anticipation.

00:22:04.500 --> 00:22:06.530
This had not just a little to do

00:22:06.530 --> 00:22:10.520
with her strange alluring
grace in those days.

00:22:10.520 --> 00:22:12.690
She walked about in such
a dreamy, distracted state

00:22:12.690 --> 00:22:15.800
that her mother let her know that
she'd check her laudanum bottle

00:22:15.800 --> 00:22:18.510
to make sure the girl
had not got into it.

00:22:18.510 --> 00:22:21.050
[ Laughter ]

00:22:21.050 --> 00:22:24.780
The afternoon before her first
dance her mother said to her,

00:22:24.780 --> 00:22:27.650
"You can't get too friendly
with these boys, Jane."

00:22:27.650 --> 00:22:31.280
Jane said nothing, just
listening, oddly calm in her way

00:22:31.280 --> 00:22:34.680
that her mother seemed
to find unsettling.

00:22:34.680 --> 00:22:37.250
So she went on, "Do you understand?

00:22:37.250 --> 00:22:39.290
You've long known it."

00:22:39.290 --> 00:22:42.920
When Jane only smiled, her stood up
in mild exasperation to walk away

00:22:42.920 --> 00:22:46.150
and as she did, she said,
"You have to be careful.

00:22:46.150 --> 00:22:49.630
It might not only be
you that gets hurt."

00:22:49.630 --> 00:22:53.800
"But Dr. Thompson said he believes
they'll be able to fix me one day.

00:22:53.800 --> 00:22:56.930
I could have a regular
life with a man someday,"

00:22:56.930 --> 00:23:00.070
though he hadn't said exactly that.

00:23:00.070 --> 00:23:03.600
Her mother stopped and looked
at her long and steady,

00:23:03.600 --> 00:23:08.800
"Believing is a matter of
faith," she said, "not certainty."

00:23:08.800 --> 00:23:11.710
Jane had never seen the look
in her eye she saw then.

00:23:11.710 --> 00:23:13.010
She looked almost empty.

00:23:13.010 --> 00:23:16.150
And for the first time Jane
could remember she saw her mother

00:23:16.150 --> 00:23:19.290
as a woman whom life had made
not just hard but also exhausted

00:23:19.290 --> 00:23:22.960
and plain, older looking
than her years.

00:23:22.960 --> 00:23:26.140
Then as if she could read the
unspoken words in Jane's eyes,

00:23:26.140 --> 00:23:28.690
her mother's expression
darkened again.

00:23:28.690 --> 00:23:32.230
Her own eyes glistened
about to shed tears,

00:23:32.230 --> 00:23:35.740
"What would you know
about life with a man?

00:23:35.740 --> 00:23:37.190
And what of your little experience

00:23:37.190 --> 00:23:41.830
in this world would make you
think it such a fine thing?"

00:23:41.830 --> 00:23:45.110
Jane watched her go out the back
door, feeling more sad for her

00:23:45.110 --> 00:23:47.440
than abashed at being abraded.

00:23:47.440 --> 00:23:48.780
Her mother's words weren't able

00:23:48.780 --> 00:23:51.240
to dispel the deeply
calm pleasure she felt

00:23:51.240 --> 00:23:54.740
in these new days, this new self.

00:23:54.740 --> 00:23:58.460
She didn't wear a diaper to the
dance, only a little padding as if

00:23:58.460 --> 00:24:00.760
for possible light menstruation

00:24:00.760 --> 00:24:02.800
so that there were no
bulky undergarments

00:24:02.800 --> 00:24:06.380
to interrupt her slim figure
or graceful movements.

00:24:06.380 --> 00:24:09.330
And she made herself a light, more
slim-fitting dress and wore a pair

00:24:09.330 --> 00:24:12.010
of shoes her father had
bought for her in town

00:24:12.010 --> 00:24:15.960
after drawing an outlined figure of
her foot on a sheet of school paper

00:24:15.960 --> 00:24:18.300
to show the shoe salesman.

00:24:18.300 --> 00:24:22.080
She attended two dances before
any of the boys got up the courage

00:24:22.080 --> 00:24:25.820
or got past their bashful
curiosity to ask her to dance.

00:24:25.820 --> 00:24:29.260 position:56%
But that was good, since it
allowed her to study their movements

00:24:29.260 --> 00:24:31.520
so she could mimic them later.

00:24:31.520 --> 00:24:34.620
And then finally, Elijah
Key did ask her.

00:24:34.620 --> 00:24:37.800
She'd seen him standing against the
wall in the shadows of dim lights

00:24:37.800 --> 00:24:41.570
from the Japanese lanterns the
organizers had hung in the hall.

00:24:41.570 --> 00:24:44.460
He wasn't wearing his glasses and
probably had no idea she was there.

00:24:44.460 --> 00:24:50.130
A little later she saw him again,
spectacles on, looking at her.

00:24:50.130 --> 00:24:52.420
Maybe someone had mentioned her.

00:24:52.420 --> 00:24:56.610
Seeing her seemed to surprise
him into something like shyness.

00:24:56.610 --> 00:25:00.050
Then when she let her attention
wander that second night,

00:25:00.050 --> 00:25:03.980
wander as it tended to do in
her state of mind, she looked up

00:25:03.980 --> 00:25:05.580
and there he was, standing
out in front of her

00:25:05.580 --> 00:25:07.490
and holding out his hand.

00:25:07.490 --> 00:25:09.160
After he danced with her,

00:25:09.160 --> 00:25:12.840
some of the other boys also began
asking her out onto the floor.

00:25:12.840 --> 00:25:16.240
She felt something that she'd
never felt before then --

00:25:16.240 --> 00:25:20.930
the pleasure of flirtation, though
she didn't even know the word.

00:25:20.930 --> 00:25:23.910
The boys liked her
and she liked them.

00:25:23.910 --> 00:25:27.430
But if any one of them seemed
about to like her too much,

00:25:27.430 --> 00:25:29.720
she had her way of
withdrawing just enough,

00:25:29.720 --> 00:25:34.110
like a scrap of paper the wind
keeps blowing just out of reach.

00:25:34.110 --> 00:25:36.530
Her oddly calm, distracted
stated seemed

00:25:36.530 --> 00:25:39.780
to fascinate them into
stupid muteness.

00:25:39.780 --> 00:25:42.100
And when she would fix
her gaze upon her partner,

00:25:42.100 --> 00:25:43.910
that boy looked dumbstruck

00:25:43.910 --> 00:25:46.940
as if thinking he might
be falling in love.

00:25:46.940 --> 00:25:50.370
