00:37:37.510 --> 00:37:41.290
of Mr. Parmenter's chickens
roasted perfectly, tiny potatoes,

00:37:41.290 --> 00:37:45.320 position:56%
string beans with almonds, chocolate
cake, a delicate discussion

00:37:45.320 --> 00:37:48.860
about her favorite music
versus Chick's Italian opera --

00:37:48.860 --> 00:37:51.850
not so different from
Miles Davis, they decided,

00:37:51.850 --> 00:37:54.260 position:56%
at least in its effects on the soul.

00:37:54.260 --> 00:37:56.670
She said she had a
drumming headache.

00:37:56.670 --> 00:37:59.390
The next morning she stood
vacantly in the kitchen,

00:37:59.390 --> 00:38:03.010
simply stared at Chick, a
block of raw bacon in her hand.

00:38:03.010 --> 00:38:04.310
"Grandma?"

00:38:04.310 --> 00:38:06.940
She grinned sheepishly,
said nothing.

00:38:06.940 --> 00:38:08.240
"Grandma?"

00:38:08.240 --> 00:38:10.690
Chick accepted the bacon
from her, put it back on ice,

00:38:10.690 --> 00:38:12.200
gathered her up in his arms --

00:38:12.200 --> 00:38:14.810
surprisingly heavy for
such a little bird --

00:38:14.810 --> 00:38:17.780
enveloped her and heaved
her up the walk to the Jeep,

00:38:17.780 --> 00:38:21.440
sat her in the passenger seat
where she retained her posture.

00:38:21.440 --> 00:38:23.240
One time his sister
had gotten stitches

00:38:23.240 --> 00:38:27.210
from a doctor somewhere near,
but he had no idea where or who.

00:38:27.210 --> 00:38:29.060
Of course, there was no phone.

00:38:29.060 --> 00:38:32.210
He drove carefully up the
hump driveway to Race Road,

00:38:32.210 --> 00:38:36.140
pulled out over the potholes at
the proper speed to beat them,

00:38:36.140 --> 00:38:39.440
drove stiffly 12 miles
to Beamis Corners --

00:38:39.440 --> 00:38:42.170
25 long minutes without
conversation.

00:38:42.170 --> 00:38:45.670
At the gas station, he pulled
in and honked loud and long.

00:38:45.670 --> 00:38:48.300
Mina flounced out,
annoyed at the honking

00:38:48.300 --> 00:38:50.390
until she saw Chick and blushed.

00:38:50.390 --> 00:38:53.120
He asked politely where
he might find a hospital.

00:38:53.120 --> 00:38:55.530
She looked at him closely,
then at grandma.

00:38:55.530 --> 00:38:58.550
"Oh my," she said, "The
hospital's in Keene [phonetic].

00:38:58.550 --> 00:38:59.850
It's 20 miles.

00:38:59.850 --> 00:39:01.460
Mrs. Flexheart?

00:39:01.460 --> 00:39:02.760
Is there a doctor?"

00:39:02.760 --> 00:39:04.280
"In Keene," I said.

00:39:04.280 --> 00:39:05.580
Chick began to panic.

00:39:05.580 --> 00:39:07.260
He said, "How do I find it?"

00:39:07.260 --> 00:39:08.950
"Oh dear," Philomena said.

00:39:08.950 --> 00:39:11.990
She patted his arms,
eyes sparkling with care.

00:39:11.990 --> 00:39:14.220
In a rush she said,
"I'll go with you."

00:39:14.220 --> 00:39:16.570
She called to her father,
who hurried from the garage

00:39:16.570 --> 00:39:18.840
at her tone, wrenches in hand.

00:39:18.840 --> 00:39:21.830
The girl quickly explained
Mrs. Flexheart was ill.

00:39:21.830 --> 00:39:25.580
Her father was as urgent as
she, tears starting to his eyes.

00:39:25.580 --> 00:39:27.030
Everyone loved grandma.

00:39:27.030 --> 00:39:30.420
Philomena climbed in the back
seat and gave directions.

00:39:30.420 --> 00:39:34.580
Chick had never driven on a highway
but found it easy once he got used

00:39:34.580 --> 00:39:38.080
to all the cars passing
him, all the honking.

00:39:38.080 --> 00:39:40.590
Mina leaned forward,
held grandma's shoulders,

00:39:40.590 --> 00:39:42.070
said, "Speed up a little."

00:39:42.070 --> 00:39:44.520
But it was hard for Chick
to go over the speed limit.

00:39:44.520 --> 00:39:48.480
Mr. Parmenter had told him for
Race Road 30 miles an hour.

00:39:48.480 --> 00:39:50.220
The girl smelled of gasoline.

00:39:50.220 --> 00:39:52.880
She put a hand on Chick's
shoulder, too.

00:39:52.880 --> 00:39:56.520
Her hair was red in the mirror, her
cheeks streaked with engine grease.

00:39:56.520 --> 00:40:00.180
He used the mirror to catch her
bright green eye for reassurance.

00:40:00.180 --> 00:40:02.660
Grandma sat very still.

00:40:02.660 --> 00:40:06.120
Thinking of other disasters
and still with no preamble,

00:40:06.120 --> 00:40:10.620
Chick unburdened himself, said, "I
saw the Shaunessy girl out there."

00:40:10.620 --> 00:40:13.600
"I've seen her, too,"
Mina said matter of fact,

00:40:13.600 --> 00:40:15.020
knowing what he meant by out there.

00:40:15.020 --> 00:40:16.320
Spruce Island, of course.

00:40:16.320 --> 00:40:20.690
She said, "Anya Shaunessy, she's so
beautiful, isn't she -- wasn't she?

00:40:20.690 --> 00:40:22.830
And her dog, I was
frightened of them, though.

00:40:22.830 --> 00:40:25.350
Purely silent, that loverly dress.

00:40:25.350 --> 00:40:27.630
I dropped my bucket and
ran right for the boat.

00:40:27.630 --> 00:40:29.170
No one believed me."

00:40:29.170 --> 00:40:31.270
She tightened her grip
on his shoulder.

00:40:31.270 --> 00:40:33.920
The trip took 40 minutes,
but they made Keene,

00:40:33.920 --> 00:40:36.360
grandma's posture perfect
the whole ride.

00:40:36.360 --> 00:40:39.310
She was silent and unblinking,
but she breathed well

00:40:39.310 --> 00:40:41.090
and Chick knew she'd be okay.

00:40:41.090 --> 00:40:43.020
At the emergency room
entrance he pulled

00:40:43.020 --> 00:40:45.380 position:56%
up perfectly, set the parking brake.

00:40:45.380 --> 00:40:49.330
He and Mina went to help grandma
out, but despite the straight spine

00:40:49.330 --> 00:40:53.020
and high chin, the open
eyes, she was unmoving.

00:40:53.020 --> 00:40:55.090
Boy and girl hefted the old woman,

00:40:55.090 --> 00:40:57.240
carried her into the
emergency room lobby.

00:40:57.240 --> 00:40:59.180
Two nurses scurried to their sides

00:40:59.180 --> 00:41:01.130
as they lay their burden
on the floor.

00:41:01.130 --> 00:41:04.610
A doctor rushed in, and then a
couple of orderlies in blue scrubs

00:41:04.610 --> 00:41:07.610
who lifted grandma onto
their gurney in a calm hurry.

00:41:07.610 --> 00:41:11.590
But after a few busy minutes,
the doctor just stopped.

00:41:11.590 --> 00:41:14.500
He set his chin, looked at Chick.

00:41:14.500 --> 00:41:16.730
The orderlies relaxed.

00:41:16.730 --> 00:41:19.170 position:56%
"I'm sorry," one of the nurses said.

00:41:19.170 --> 00:41:23.280
Philomena burst into hot
tears; Chick then, too.

00:41:23.280 --> 00:41:26.540
Shocked and weeping, standing among
strangers, it was only natural

00:41:26.540 --> 00:41:29.490
that he and Mina caught one
another in a tight embrace,

00:41:29.490 --> 00:41:32.240
the nurse then folding
them both in her own arms,

00:41:32.240 --> 00:41:34.710
then an orderly joining
in, then the doctor --

00:41:34.710 --> 00:41:37.550
a long group hug, protocol
abandoned,

00:41:37.550 --> 00:41:39.180
all of them in their humanity.

00:41:39.180 --> 00:41:42.860
Mina's father arrived with
Mr. Parmenter in short order.

00:41:42.860 --> 00:41:45.430
Chick had never seen a man cry

00:41:45.430 --> 00:41:48.580
like Mr. Parmenter cried
when he heard the news.

00:41:48.580 --> 00:41:51.620
The old bird dropped to
his knees, held his face,

00:41:51.620 --> 00:41:53.930
sobbed and gulped inconsolably,

00:41:53.930 --> 00:41:57.610
so devastated that even an hour
later he couldn't drive the Jeep

00:41:57.610 --> 00:42:00.950
home but had to ride with
Mr. Hardy, Mina and Chick

00:42:00.950 --> 00:42:04.300
in the broad back seat of
the mechanic's ancient Woody,

00:42:04.300 --> 00:42:08.190
her foot hooked stealthily
around Chick's calf,

00:42:08.190 --> 00:42:10.350
their fingers tightly interlaced,

00:42:10.350 --> 00:42:13.600
sweaty after a while,
almost painful, too.

00:42:13.600 --> 00:42:14.900
It didn't matter.

00:42:14.900 --> 00:42:17.010
They weren't going to let go.

